        .line 
        .articleBody.clear
            p 
              | The bookmark above actually is javascript code that can be injected to any HTML page to perform some task.
              | The task is to ask for the string passphrase, generate key, and encrypt or decrypt focused textarea. We use 
              a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advanced_Encryption_Standard",target="_new",rel="nofollow") AES 
              | encryption with
              a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PBKDF2", target="new", rel="nofollow") PBKDF2 
              | key generation.
              | The text is encrypted and decrypted locally, without external server.
            p
              | However, because of encryption code still loaded from the server, there is can be 
              a(href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man-in-the-middle_attack",rel="nofollow") man-in-the-middle 
              | attack.
              | So please check that your HTTPS connection certificate is valid.
              | If you see alert (like red HTTPS on my instruction images), please stop use the tool and send me note!
